InspireNOLA Charter Schools
May 12 at 3:00 PM ·

Senior pickup will take place at our three high schools on May 13th from 9 to 11 am. There will be staggered pickup times based on last names.

Staggered pickup times:
9:00-9:30am: last name beginning with A – F
9:30-10:00am: last name beginning with G – L
10:00-10:30am: last name beginning with M – R
10:30-11:00am: last name beginning with S – Z

During this time, seniors will pick up their unofficial transcript, senior yard signs and other items. All students/ parents must stay in their cars and join the pick up line when they arrive.

shared_text:
InspireNOLA Charter Schools
March 13 at 3:55 PM ·

Beginning Wednesday, March 18, InspireNOLA will provide meals to anyone 18 or below, from any school. InspireNOLA will set up two hubs to serve grab-and-go breakfast and lunches. Meals will be available Monday through Friday, from 9am to 12pm.

The hub locations are:

• Westbank – Alice Harte Charter School – 5300 Berkley Dr. New Orleans, LA 70131
• Eastbank – McDonogh #35 High School – 4000 Cadillac St. New Orleans, LA 70122

Please note: As other locations for meals become available across the city, we will post an updated list on our website and social media.

For more information visit, http://www.inspirenolacharterschools.org/coronavirus.

#InspireNOLA #NOLAEd

Beautiful, painful and necessary. McMain sophomore Anana Ezeb shows composure well beyond her years serenading the mother of her classmate, 15-year-old Chance Smith, at a rally to end gun violence in New Orleans. Smith was shot and killed Saturday. A 17-year-old has been arrested and charged with second degree murder for his death.
